'''Charles Herbert Wilson''' ([[February 15]], [[1917]]-[[July 21]], [[1984]]) was a California congressman from the [[Los Angeles]] area.  He served as representative between 1963 and 1981.  In 1980, he was [[censure|censured]] by the House for "financial misconduct" stemming from the so-called "[[Koreagate]]" scandal.

